50  /**
51   * A {@link org.xml.sax.ContentHandler ContentHandler} that transforms XML
52   * document into Java class file. This class can be feeded by any kind of SAX
53   * 2.0 event producers, e.g. XML parser, XSLT or XPath engines, or custom code.
54   * 
55   * @see org.apache.tapestry5.internal.plastic.asm.xml.SAXClassAdapter
56   * @see org.apache.tapestry5.internal.plastic.asm.xml.Processor
57   * 
58   * @author Eugene Kuleshov
59   */
60  public class ASMContentHandler extends DefaultHandler implements Opcodes {

327     /**
328      * Constructs a new {@link ASMContentHandler ASMContentHandler} object.
329      * 
330      * @param cv
331      *            class visitor that will be called to reconstruct the classfile
332      *            using the XML stream.
333      */
334     public ASMContentHandler(final ClassVisitor cv) {
335         this.cv = cv;
336     }

338     /**
339      * Process notification of the start of an XML element being reached.
340      * 
341      * @param ns
342      *            - The Namespace URI, or the empty string if the element has no
343      *            Namespace URI or if Namespace processing is not being
344      *            performed.
345      * @param lName
346      *            - The local name (without prefix), or the empty string if
347      *            Namespace processing is not being performed.
348      * @param qName
349      *            - The qualified name (with prefix), or the empty string if
350      *            qualified names are not available.
351      * @param list
352      *            - The attributes attached to the element. If there are no
353      *            attributes, it shall be an empty Attributes object.
354      * @exception SAXException
355      *                if a parsing error is to be reported
356      */
357     @Override
358     public final void startElement(final String ns, final String lName,
359             final String qName, final Attributes list) throws SAXException {
360         // the actual element name is either in lName or qName, depending
361         // on whether the parser is namespace aware
362         String name = lName == null || lName.length() == 0 ? qName : lName;
363 
364         // Compute the current matching rule
365         StringBuffer sb = new StringBuffer(match);
366         if (match.length() > 0) {
367             sb.append('/');
368         }
369         sb.append(name);
370         match = sb.toString();
371 
372         // Fire "begin" events for all relevant rules
373         Rule r = (Rule) RULES.match(match);
374         if (r != null) {
375             r.begin(name, list);
376         }
377     }
378 
379     /**
380      * Process notification of the end of an XML element being reached.
381      * 
382      * @param ns
383      *            - The Namespace URI, or the empty string if the element has no
384      *            Namespace URI or if Namespace processing is not being
385      *            performed.
386      * @param lName
387      *            - The local name (without prefix), or the empty string if
388      *            Namespace processing is not being performed.
389      * @param qName
390      *            - The qualified XML 1.0 name (with prefix), or the empty
391      *            string if qualified names are not available.
392      * 
393      * @exception SAXException
394      *                if a parsing error is to be reported
395      */
396     @Override
397     public final void endElement(final String ns, final String lName,
398             final String qName) throws SAXException {
399         // the actual element name is either in lName or qName, depending
400         // on whether the parser is namespace aware
401         String name = lName == null || lName.length() == 0 ? qName : lName;
402 
403         // Fire "end" events for all relevant rules in reverse order
404         Rule r = (Rule) RULES.match(match);
405         if (r != null) {
406             r.end(name);
407         }
408 
409         // Recover the previous match expression
410         int slash = match.lastIndexOf('/');
411         if (slash >= 0) {
412             match = match.substring(0, slash);
413         } else {
414             match = "";
415         }
416     }
417 
418     /**
419      * Return the top object on the stack without removing it. If there are no
420      * objects on the stack, return <code>null</code>.
421      * 
422      * @return the top object on the stack without removing it.
423      */
424     final Object peek() {
425         int size = stack.size();
426         return size == 0 ? null : stack.get(size - 1);
427     }
428 
429     /**
430      * Pop the top object off of the stack, and return it. If there are no
431      * objects on the stack, return <code>null</code>.
432      * 
433      * @return the top object off of the stack.
434      */
435     final Object pop() {
436         int size = stack.size();
437         return size == 0 ? null : stack.remove(size - 1);
438     }
439 
440     /**
441      * Push a new object onto the top of the object stack.
442      * 
443      * @param object
444      *            The new object
445      */
446     final void push(final Object object) {
447         stack.add(object);
448     }
449 
450     static final class RuleSet {
451 
452         private final HashMap<String, Object> rules = new HashMap<String, Object>();
453 
454         private final ArrayList<String> lpatterns = new ArrayList<String>();
455 
456         private final ArrayList<String> rpatterns = new ArrayList<String>();
457 
458         public void add(final String path, final Object rule) {
459             String pattern = path;
460             if (path.startsWith("*/")) {
461                 pattern = path.substring(1);
462                 lpatterns.add(pattern);
463             } else if (path.endsWith("/*")) {
464                 pattern = path.substring(0, path.length() - 1);
465                 rpatterns.add(pattern);
466             }
467             rules.put(pattern, rule);
468         }
469 
470         public Object match(final String path) {
471             if (rules.containsKey(path)) {
472                 return rules.get(path);
473             }
474 
475             int n = path.lastIndexOf('/');
476             for (Iterator<String> it = lpatterns.iterator(); it.hasNext();) {
477                 String pattern = it.next();
478                 if (path.substring(n).endsWith(pattern)) {
479                     return rules.get(pattern);
480                 }
481             }
482 
483             for (Iterator<String> it = rpatterns.iterator(); it.hasNext();) {
484                 String pattern = it.next();
485                 if (path.startsWith(pattern)) {
486                     return rules.get(pattern);
487                 }
488             }
489 
490             return null;
491         }
492     }
493 
494     /**
495      * Rule
496      */
497     protected abstract class Rule {
498 
499         public void begin(final String name, final Attributes attrs)
500                 throws SAXException {
501         }
502 
503         public void end(final String name) {
504         }
505 
506         protected final Object getValue(final String desc, final String val)
507                 throws SAXException {
508             Object value = null;
509             if (val != null) {
510                 if ("Ljava/lang/String;".equals(desc)) {
511                     value = decode(val);
512                 } else if ("Ljava/lang/Integer;".equals(desc)
513                         || "I".equals(desc) || "S".equals(desc)
514                         || "B".equals(desc) || "C".equals(desc)
515                         || "Z".equals(desc)) {
516                     value = new Integer(val);
517 
518                 } else if ("Ljava/lang/Short;".equals(desc)) {
519                     value = new Short(val);
520 
521                 } else if ("Ljava/lang/Byte;".equals(desc)) {
522                     value = new Byte(val);
523 
524                 } else if ("Ljava/lang/Character;".equals(desc)) {
525                     value = new Character(decode(val).charAt(0));
526 
527                 } else if ("Ljava/lang/Boolean;".equals(desc)) {
528                     value = Boolean.valueOf(val);
529 
530                 } else if ("Ljava/lang/Long;".equals(desc) || "J".equals(desc)) {
531                     value = new Long(val);
532                 } else if ("Ljava/lang/Float;".equals(desc) || "F".equals(desc)) {
533                     value = new Float(val);
534                 } else if ("Ljava/lang/Double;".equals(desc)
535                         || "D".equals(desc)) {
536                     value = new Double(val);
537                 } else if (Type.getDescriptor(Type.class).equals(desc)) {
538                     value = Type.getType(val);
539 
540                 } else if (Type.getDescriptor(Handle.class).equals(desc)) {
541                     value = decodeHandle(val);
542 
543                 } else {
544                     // TODO use of default toString().
545                     throw new SAXException("Invalid value:" + val + " desc:"
546                             + desc + " ctx:" + this);
547                 }
548             }
549             return value;
550         }
551 
552         Handle decodeHandle(final String val) throws SAXException {
553             try {
554                 int dotIndex = val.indexOf('.');
555                 int descIndex = val.indexOf('(', dotIndex + 1);
556                 int tagIndex = val.lastIndexOf('(');
557 
558                 int tag = Integer.parseInt(val.substring(tagIndex + 1,
559                         val.length() - 1));
560                 String owner = val.substring(0, dotIndex);
561                 String name = val.substring(dotIndex + 1, descIndex);
562                 String desc = val.substring(descIndex, tagIndex - 1);
563                 return new Handle(tag, owner, name, desc);
564 
565             } catch (RuntimeException e) {
566                 throw new SAXException("Malformed handle " + val, e);
567             }
568         }
569 
570         private final String decode(final String val) throws SAXException {
571             StringBuffer sb = new StringBuffer(val.length());
572             try {
573                 int n = 0;
574                 while (n < val.length()) {
575                     char c = val.charAt(n);
576                     if (c == '\\') {
577                         n++;
578                         c = val.charAt(n);
579                         if (c == '\\') {
580                             sb.append('\\');
581                         } else {
582                             n++; // skip 'u'
583                             sb.append((char) Integer.parseInt(
584                                     val.substring(n, n + 4), 16));
585                             n += 3;
586                         }
587                     } else {
588                         sb.append(c);
589                     }
590                     n++;
591                 }
592 
593             } catch (RuntimeException ex) {
594                 throw new SAXException(ex);
595             }
596             return sb.toString();
597         }
598 
599         protected final Label getLabel(final Object label) {
600             Label lbl = labels.get(label);
601             if (lbl == null) {
602                 lbl = new Label();
603                 labels.put(label, lbl);
604             }
605             return lbl;
606         }
607 
608         // TODO verify move to stack
609         protected final MethodVisitor getCodeVisitor() {
610             return (MethodVisitor) peek();
611         }
612 
613         protected final int getAccess(final String s) {
614             int access = 0;
615             if (s.indexOf("public") != -1) {
616                 access |= ACC_PUBLIC;
617             }
618             if (s.indexOf("private") != -1) {
619                 access |= ACC_PRIVATE;
620             }
621             if (s.indexOf("protected") != -1) {
622                 access |= ACC_PROTECTED;
623             }
624             if (s.indexOf("static") != -1) {
625                 access |= ACC_STATIC;
626             }
627             if (s.indexOf("final") != -1) {
628                 access |= ACC_FINAL;
629             }
630             if (s.indexOf("super") != -1) {
631                 access |= ACC_SUPER;
632             }
633             if (s.indexOf("synchronized") != -1) {
634                 access |= ACC_SYNCHRONIZED;
635             }
636             if (s.indexOf("volatile") != -1) {
637                 access |= ACC_VOLATILE;
638             }
639             if (s.indexOf("bridge") != -1) {
640                 access |= ACC_BRIDGE;
641             }
642             if (s.indexOf("varargs") != -1) {
643                 access |= ACC_VARARGS;
644             }
645             if (s.indexOf("transient") != -1) {
646                 access |= ACC_TRANSIENT;
647             }
648             if (s.indexOf("native") != -1) {
649                 access |= ACC_NATIVE;
650             }
651             if (s.indexOf("interface") != -1) {
652                 access |= ACC_INTERFACE;
653             }
654             if (s.indexOf("abstract") != -1) {
655                 access |= ACC_ABSTRACT;
656             }
657             if (s.indexOf("strict") != -1) {
658                 access |= ACC_STRICT;
659             }
660             if (s.indexOf("synthetic") != -1) {
661                 access |= ACC_SYNTHETIC;
662             }
663             if (s.indexOf("annotation") != -1) {
664                 access |= ACC_ANNOTATION;
665             }
666             if (s.indexOf("enum") != -1) {
667                 access |= ACC_ENUM;
668             }
669             if (s.indexOf("deprecated") != -1) {
670                 access |= ACC_DEPRECATED;
671             }
672             if (s.indexOf("mandated") != -1) {
673                 access |= ACC_MANDATED;
674             }
675             return access;
676         }
677     }

950      * FrameRule
951      */
952     final class FrameRule extends Rule {
953 
954         @Override
955         public void begin(final String name, final Attributes attrs) {
956             HashMap<String, Object> typeLists = new HashMap<String, Object>();
957             typeLists.put("local", new ArrayList<Object>());
958             typeLists.put("stack", new ArrayList<Object>());
959             push(attrs.getValue("type"));
960             push(attrs.getValue("count") == null ? "0" : attrs
961                     .getValue("count"));
962             push(typeLists);
963         }
964 
965         @Override
966         public void end(final String name) {
967             HashMap<?, ?> typeLists = (HashMap<?, ?>) pop();
968             ArrayList<?> locals = (ArrayList<?>) typeLists.get("local");
969             int nLocal = locals.size();
970             Object[] local = locals.toArray();
971             ArrayList<?> stacks = (ArrayList<?>) typeLists.get("stack");
972             int nStack = stacks.size();
973             Object[] stack = stacks.toArray();
974             String count = (String) pop();
975             String type = (String) pop();
976             if ("NEW".equals(type)) {
977                 getCodeVisitor()
978                         .visitFrame(F_NEW, nLocal, local, nStack, stack);
979             } else if ("FULL".equals(type)) {
980                 getCodeVisitor().visitFrame(F_FULL, nLocal, local, nStack,
981                         stack);
982             } else if ("APPEND".equals(type)) {
983                 getCodeVisitor().visitFrame(F_APPEND, nLocal, local, 0, null);
984             } else if ("CHOP".equals(type)) {
985                 getCodeVisitor().visitFrame(F_CHOP, Integer.parseInt(count),
986                         null, 0, null);
987             } else if ("SAME".equals(type)) {
988                 getCodeVisitor().visitFrame(F_SAME, 0, null, 0, null);
989             } else if ("SAME1".equals(type)) {
990                 getCodeVisitor().visitFrame(F_SAME1, 0, null, nStack, stack);
991             }
992         }
993     }

997         @Override
998         public void begin(final String name, final Attributes attrs) {

1001                     .get(name);

1003             if ("uninitialized".equals(type)) {
1004                 types.add(getLabel(attrs.getValue("label")));
1005             } else {
1006                 Integer t = TYPES.get(type);
1007                 if (t == null) {
1008                     types.add(type);
1009                 } else {
1010                     types.add(t);
1011                 }
1012             }
1013         }

1110     /**
1111      * OpcodesRule
1112      */
1113     final class OpcodesRule extends Rule {
1114 
1115         // public boolean match( String match, String element) {
1116         // return match.startsWith( path) && OPCODES.containsKey( element);
1117         // }
1118 
1119         @Override
1120         public final void begin(final String element, final Attributes attrs)
1121                 throws SAXException {
1122             Opcode o = OPCODES.get(element);
1123             if (o == null) {
1124                 throw new SAXException("Invalid element: " + element + " at "
1125                         + match);
1126             }
1127 
1128             switch (o.type) {
1129             case OpcodeGroup.INSN:
1130                 getCodeVisitor().visitInsn(o.opcode);
1131                 break;
1132 
1133             case OpcodeGroup.INSN_FIELD:
1134                 getCodeVisitor().visitFieldInsn(o.opcode,
1135                         attrs.getValue("owner"), attrs.getValue("name"),
1136                         attrs.getValue("desc"));
1137                 break;
1138 
1139             case OpcodeGroup.INSN_INT:
1140                 getCodeVisitor().visitIntInsn(o.opcode,
1141                         Integer.parseInt(attrs.getValue("value")));
1142                 break;
1143 
1144             case OpcodeGroup.INSN_JUMP:
1145                 getCodeVisitor().visitJumpInsn(o.opcode,
1146                         getLabel(attrs.getValue("label")));
1147                 break;
1148 
1149             case OpcodeGroup.INSN_METHOD:
1150                 getCodeVisitor().visitMethodInsn(o.opcode,
1151                         attrs.getValue("owner"), attrs.getValue("name"),
1152                         attrs.getValue("desc"),
1153                         attrs.getValue("itf").equals("true"));
1154                 break;
1155 
1156             case OpcodeGroup.INSN_TYPE:
1157                 getCodeVisitor()
1158                         .visitTypeInsn(o.opcode, attrs.getValue("desc"));
1159                 break;
1160 
1161             case OpcodeGroup.INSN_VAR:
1162                 getCodeVisitor().visitVarInsn(o.opcode,
1163                         Integer.parseInt(attrs.getValue("var")));
1164                 break;
1165 
1166             case OpcodeGroup.INSN_IINC:
1167                 getCodeVisitor().visitIincInsn(
1168                         Integer.parseInt(attrs.getValue("var")),
1169                         Integer.parseInt(attrs.getValue("inc")));
1170                 break;
1171 
1172             case OpcodeGroup.INSN_LDC:
1173                 getCodeVisitor()
1174                         .visitLdcInsn(
1175                                 getValue(attrs.getValue("desc"),
1176                                         attrs.getValue("cst")));
1177                 break;
1178 
1179             case OpcodeGroup.INSN_MULTIANEWARRAY:
1180                 getCodeVisitor().visitMultiANewArrayInsn(
1181                         attrs.getValue("desc"),
1182                         Integer.parseInt(attrs.getValue("dims")));
1183                 break;
1184 
1185             default:
1186                 throw new Error("Internal error");
1187 
1188             }
1189         }
1190     }

1235         public void begin(final String name, final Attributes attrs) {
1236             String desc = attrs.getValue("desc");
1237             boolean visible = Boolean.valueOf(attrs.getValue("visible"))
1238                     .booleanValue();
1239             int typeRef = Integer.parseInt(attrs.getValue("typeRef"));
1240             TypePath typePath = TypePath.fromString(attrs.getValue("typePath"));
1241 
1242             Object v = peek();
1243             if (v instanceof ClassVisitor) {
1244                 push(((ClassVisitor) v).visitTypeAnnotation(typeRef, typePath,
1245                         desc, visible));
1246             } else if (v instanceof FieldVisitor) {
1247                 push(((FieldVisitor) v).visitTypeAnnotation(typeRef, typePath,
1248                         desc, visible));
1249             } else if (v instanceof MethodVisitor) {
1250                 push(((MethodVisitor) v).visitTypeAnnotation(typeRef, typePath,
1251                         desc, visible));
1252             }
1253         }
1254 
1255         @Override
1256         public void end(final String name) {
1257             AnnotationVisitor av = (AnnotationVisitor) pop();
1258             if (av != null) {
1259                 av.visitEnd();
1260             }
1261         }

1330     final class LocalVariableAnnotationRule extends Rule {
1331 
1332         @Override
1333         public void begin(final String name, final Attributes attrs) {
1334             String desc = attrs.getValue("desc");
1335             boolean visible = Boolean.valueOf(attrs.getValue("visible"))
1336                     .booleanValue();
1337             int typeRef = Integer.parseInt(attrs.getValue("typeRef"));
1338             TypePath typePath = TypePath.fromString(attrs.getValue("typePath"));
1339             String[] s = attrs.getValue("start").split(" ");
1340             Label[] start = new Label[s.length];
1341             for (int i = 0; i < start.length; ++i) {
1342                 start[i] = getLabel(s[i]);
1343             }
1344             String[] e = attrs.getValue("end").split(" ");
1345             Label[] end = new Label[e.length];
1346             for (int i = 0; i < end.length; ++i) {
1347                 end[i] = getLabel(e[i]);
1348             }
1349             String[] v = attrs.getValue("index").split(" ");
1350             int[] index = new int[v.length];
1351             for (int i = 0; i < index.length; ++i) {
1352                 index[i] = Integer.parseInt(v[i]);
1353             }
1354             push(((MethodVisitor) peek()).visitLocalVariableAnnotation(typeRef,
1355                     typePath, start, end, index, desc, visible));
1356         }
1357 
1358         @Override
1359         public void end(final String name) {
1360             AnnotationVisitor av = (AnnotationVisitor) pop();
1361             if (av != null) {
1362                 av.visitEnd();
1363             }
1364         }
1365     }
